<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFFAFF93FEB1FB5DFE6F526B" box="[256,418,1268,1294]" name="Argentina" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">ARGENTINA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFFAFF93FE1EFB5DFD78526B" box="[431,693,1268,1294]" country="Argentina" name="Buenos Aires" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Buenos Aires Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<quantity id="4CFB9B23FFFAFF93FD72FB5DFCC1526B" box="[707,780,1268,1294]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" unit="km" value="20.0">20 km</quantity>
SE of Olavarria; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFFAFF93FC64FB5DFB49526B" box="[981,1156,1268,1294]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="2010-01-02">2 January 2010</date>
; 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFFAFF93FB23FB5DFB6A526B" box="[1170,1191,1268,1294]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">R</collectionCode>
. Ruiz. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FA8DFB5DFE1A5257" authority="(Holmberg)" baseAuthorityName="Holmberg" baseAuthorityYear="1875" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Polybetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pythagoricus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFAFF93FA8DFB5DFE815254" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Polybetes pythagoricus</emphasis>
(Holmberg)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FE55FABEFDA15257" box="[484,620,1303,1330]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sparassidae</taxonomicName>
), adult female. The wasp pulled the paralyzed huntsman spider backwards up a vertical brick wall, holding it dorsal side upward and grasping its left pedipalp with her mandibles (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFAFF93FADBFA93FF305212" author="Ruiz RO" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref26645" refString="Ruiz RO. 2010. Arana vs avispa. Available at https: // www. flickr. com / photos / roruiz / 5107766300 / in / dateposted /. (Last accessed 14 January 2021)." type="url" year="2010">Ruiz 2010</bibRefCitation>
). This wasp was initially identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FD28FAF4FB90521D" authority="(Taschenberg)" baseAuthorityName="Taschenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[665,1117,1373,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Tachypompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFAFF93FD28FAF4FC7A5212" box="[665,951,1373,1399]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Tachypompilus erubescens</emphasis>
(Taschenberg)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFAFF93FB30FAF4FA50521D" author="Kurczewski FE &amp; West RC &amp; Waichert C &amp; Kissane KC &amp; Ubick D &amp; Pitts JP" box="[1153,1437,1373,1400]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref25112" refString="Kurczewski FE, West RC, Waichert C, Kissane KC, Ubick D, Pitts JP. 2020 b. New and unusual host records for North American and South American spider wasps (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Zootaxa 4891: 1 - 112." type="journal article" year="2020">Kurczewski et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFFAFF93FEB1FA29FC225160" blockId="15.[191,1441,1230,1681]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFFAFF93FEB1FA29FE6F52FF" box="[256,418,1408,1434]" name="Argentina" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">ARGENTINA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFFAFF93FE1DFA28FD6752FF" box="[428,682,1408,1435]" country="Argentina" name="Buenos Aires" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Buenos Aires Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<quantity id="4CFB9B23FFFAFF93FD05FA29FD2052FF" box="[692,749,1408,1434]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" unit="km" value="4.0">4 km</quantity>
N of San Clemente del Tuyú; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFFAFF93FB87FA29FAC452FF" box="[1078,1289,1408,1434]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="2014-12-26">26 December 2014</date>
; J. F. Romero. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FEB5FA0AFE3652D8" baseAuthorityName="Holmberg" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[260,507,1443,1469]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Polybetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pythagoricus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFAFF93FEB5FA0AFE3652D8" box="[260,507,1443,1469]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Polybetes pythagoricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, adult female. The wasp dragged the paralyzed huntsman spider backwards on the ground, dorsal side upward, grasping its right pedipalp with her mandibles (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFAFF93FBAEFA6EFB735284" author="Romero JF" box="[1055,1214,1479,1505]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref26489" refString="Romero JF. 2014. Supervivencia - The Winner. Available at https: // www. flickr. com / photos / juliofromero / 15971305028 / in / dateposted /. (Last accessed 14 January 2021)." type="url" year="2014">Romero 2014</bibRefCitation>
). This wasp was initially identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FE3DFA43FD665161" baseAuthorityName="Taschenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[396,683,1514,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Tachypompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFAFF93FE3DFA43FD665161" box="[396,683,1514,1540]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Tachypompilus erubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFAFF93FD7EFA43FC265160" author="Kurczewski FE &amp; West RC &amp; Waichert C &amp; Kissane KC &amp; Ubick D &amp; Pitts JP" box="[719,1003,1514,1541]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref25112" refString="Kurczewski FE, West RC, Waichert C, Kissane KC, Ubick D, Pitts JP. 2020 b. New and unusual host records for North American and South American spider wasps (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Zootaxa 4891: 1 - 112." type="journal article" year="2020">Kurczewski et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFFAFF93FEB1F9A4FE3651F4" blockId="15.[191,1441,1230,1681]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFFAFF93FEB1F9A4FE6F5142" box="[256,418,1549,1575]" name="Argentina" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">ARGENTINA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFFAFF93FE1FF9A4FD4E5142" box="[430,643,1549,1575]" country="Argentina" name="Neuquen" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Neuquén Province</collectingRegion>
, Pichilemu; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFFAFF93FCA1F9A4FC2A5142" box="[784,999,1549,1575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="2014-12-30">30 December 2014</date>
; M. Belgrano. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FB67F9A4FF38512F" baseAuthorityName="Holmberg" baseAuthorityYear="1875" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Polybetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pythagoricus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFAFF93FB67F9A4FF38512F" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Polybetes pythagoricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, adult or subadult female. The wasp examined the paralyzed huntsman spider with her antennae as it laid dorsal side upward on the ground (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFAFF93FDF3F9FAFD275108" author="Belgrano M." box="[578,746,1619,1645]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="15762656873" refId="ref21287" refString="Belgrano M. 2014. La avispa (San Jorge) y la arana. Available athttps: // www. flickr. com / photos / 130186250 @ N 07 / 15762656873 / in / photostream. (Last accessed 14 January 2021)." type="journal article" year="2014">Belgrano 2014</bibRefCitation>
). This wasp was initially identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FB30F9FAFA525108" baseAuthorityName="Taschenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[1153,1439,1619,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Tachypompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFAFF93FB30F9FAFA525108" box="[1153,1439,1619,1645]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Tachypompilus erubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFAFF93FF50F9DFFE3651F4" author="Kurczewski FE &amp; West RC &amp; Waichert C &amp; Kissane KC &amp; Ubick D &amp; Pitts JP" box="[225,507,1654,1681]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref25112" refString="Kurczewski FE, West RC, Waichert C, Kissane KC, Ubick D, Pitts JP. 2020 b. New and unusual host records for North American and South American spider wasps (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Zootaxa 4891: 1 - 112." type="journal article" year="2020">Kurczewski et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
